By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Presidential Candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, (PDP) and National Chairman of the party, Prince Uche Secondus have charged the people of the north east to join the rest of the country in the party’s mission to rescue the nation. The two spoke on Tuesday at the North East zonal rally of the party in Gombe, Gombe state as jubilant crowd drawn from the six states of the zone welcomed them. According to the statement signed by the SA media office signed by Ike Abonyi, Prince Secondus said that the economy of the nation has been destroyed by the APC administration with President Muhammadu Buhari painting a gory picture. Alhaji Atiku said that the situation in the country since the All Progressives Congress, (APC) came to power calls for all hands to be on deck to rescue our democracy. The National Chairman of the party on his part charged the people to be ready to vote out the APC by coming out on the voting day. “You must not only vote but must be ready to defend your vote, the APC is not preparing for election, they want to rig but you must be ready to resist their antics. Prince Secondus said that APC has destroyed the country and PDP and Atiku are coming back to power to save situation. He said Atiku is coming with all the prerequisite experience both in public and private sector to restore the nation’s lost glory. The speaker of the House of Representatives’ Hon. Yakubu Dogara also addressed the rally that was attended by top PDP stakeholders including the Deputy Senate President Ike Ekkweremadu. The National Chairman performed the symbolic handing over of flag to the Presidential candidate and the six gubernatorial candidates of Gombe, Adamawa, Taraba, Borno, Yobe and Buachi states that make up the geo political zone. 